✅ COMPREHENSIVE TAKEAWAYS: MULTI-FACTOR MODELS WITH PYMDP INTEGRATION
================================================================================
🤖 PyMDP Multi-Factor Agent integration successful - Complex state space demonstrated!

🔍 MULTI-FACTOR MODEL FOUNDATIONS:
1. Factorized states decompose complex environments into manageable factors
2. Independent factors can be inferred separately (efficient)
3. Dependent factors require joint inference (more complex but richer)
4. Hierarchical factors enable structured, multi-level reasoning
5. Marginal inference extracts single-factor beliefs from joint posteriors
6. Factor interactions capture realistic environmental dependencies

🚀 PYMDP AGENT INTEGRATION:
7. Agent class efficiently handles complex multi-factor state spaces
8. Multi-factor observations capture rich environmental dependencies
9. Factorized representations provide dramatic parameter efficiency gains
10. Multi-factor inference captures complex inter-factor dependencies
11. Control over multiple factors enables sophisticated behavioral repertoires
12. PyMDP obj_array structure naturally supports multi-factor architectures

